#Approach:

Approach (Detect Cycle in Linked List - Floyd Algorithm):

1. Do pointer use karte hain: slow aur fast.
2. Slow 1 step move karega, fast 2 step move karega.
3. Agar linked list me cycle hoga, to fast pointer slow ko pakad lega
   (matlab dono kisi point par mil jayenge).
4. Agar cycle nahi hoga, to fast pointer null ho jayega.
5. Loop condition: fast != null && fast.next != null
6. Agar slow == fast ho jaye, return true.
7. Loop khatam ho jaye to return false.

Main Idea:
- Fast pointer slow se tez hai, isliye cycle me pakad lega.

Time Complexity: O(N)
Space Complexity: O(1)

#Code:

/**
 * Definition for singly-linked list.
 * class ListNode {
 *     int val;
 *     ListNode next;
 *     ListNode(int x) {
 *         val = x;
 *         next = null;
 *     }
 * }
 */
public class Solution {
    public boolean hasCycle(ListNode head) {

        if(head == null || head.next == null){
            return false;
        }

        ListNode slow = head;
        ListNode fast = head;

        while(fast != null && fast.next != null){
            slow = slow.next;
            fast = fast.next.next;

            if(slow == fast){
                return true;
            }
        }
        return false;
        
    }
}
